cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with understanding visual scenes and images, which is a core area of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of Support Vector Machines (SVM) for detecting relations between objects in an image falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to detect relationships between objects in an image. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with image captioning and story generation, which are related to natural language processing. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The context of an image can be used for similar image retrieval, which falls under the domain of information retrieval.
